snippet.textDisplay:
For those of you who understand Russian I have to recommend Ukrainian youtuber "Рома, просто Рома" . He just tested some competitor on mobile Core i7U(4/8!) and found out that, in this particular case, single-channelled RAM actually draws back performance dramatically! Both cases, work and gaming, actual performance drop goes up to 40% loss bc of bandwidth holdback for ANY CPU/IGP/APU on relatively slow and high-latenced memory. Would be great to have some discrete graphics or, at least, dual channel...
Anyway, thank you Linus!!!
